<br>
war/cleric/enc is your foundation, then go for all dps.  mages and necros are great because their pets don't miss a beat even if slight ping pong occurs.  AM3 rangers are awesome, monks, and rogues (can't ping pong at all)  <br>
<br>
make hot key for calling out if you are slowed, use /shield and ae taunt judiciously but don't be afraid to blow it when necessary.  you have maybe 5 extra seconds on the first mob of every wave so try to save mana there.  but once you have aquired a target, don't switch for ANY reason.  and of course, try to get rock golems first.  <br>
<br>
now make a hot key that calls out for extra nukes.  this will signal your enc and cleric to nuke the mob once and notify the others in the group that it's getting too close for comfort.  the thing i use to determine whether to call extra nuke is when the executioner askes if the prisoner has any last words.  if by then the mob im on isn't below 40% health, i call the nuke.  and if it's above 50%, i spam that key.  don't worry about their mana, because if the mob doesn't die in time, you fail anyways, so you might as well try to go as far as you can.  <br>
<br>
