<br>
Yes you need massive DPS for the waves but you need someone to absorb some massive hits on the boss to succeed.<br>
<br>
I did my trials in a pick up group. I am now level 65.<br>
<br>
I go back to justice to help on occasion, because friends need tanks.<br>
<br>
Here is a hint to raise your DPS a little too.<br>
Use a high end 2 handed weapon.<br>
<br>
Yeah I know 99% of the warrior population out there feel that 2 fast 1 handed weapons are the only way to go.<br>
<br>
I will put my 85 Average DPS against any other warrior out there. <br>
I parse out the damage done by other warriors that I group or raid with as well and find that the average DPS for a Blade of Carnage and another like weapon is only around 65 DPS.<br>
<br>
With full ranger and shaman buffs I get my average DPS to around 95 DPS.<br>
<br>
I use a WindBlade.<br>
<br>
For taunting I still pull out the old fast 1 handers with the taunt procs, but for PURE Damage out put - like what is needed in the trials I can more then carry my own weight. <p><p><table width="687" border="0">
