<br>
the key is cleric melee .... <br>
<br>
it may sound ghay, but bear with me .... with the insane procs on the new cleric hammer, they put out near bard damage in melee. (i tried to get my group to let the cleric melee for the first 2, but they wouldnt believe me, when we came outta the 3rd with some flags, they understood)<br>
<br>
Failed twice with the same group, third time went in, Cleric broke out uba hammer, and started poundin on stuff.  (only the waves, he was healing me like a mo fo when the boss popped)<br>
<br>
Take 1 warrior, 1 cleric, 1 chanter, and damage, you should be fine ... <br>
<br>
and dont worry bout taunting before breaking mez, takes too long, just pound on stuff, and make sure the damage is on the same target. (tell your chanter to memblur after he mezzes)<br>
<br>
Pick your target as soon as possible, i usually pan out with f9 to pick my next target about halfway through the mob, just so i know where im going, and relay it to my group, so they all know where im headed ... its always a good idea to know before hand what to attack, that way you dont waste time between kills deciding.<br>
<br>
you only have ~30 seconds per mob<br>
<br>
Rocks first ... then the funguslizardguys<br>
<br>
Mages own the trials, the rockfiend looking things can be banished. <p>Master Xith N'Shezbenon<br>
